HEADWORD: geraniol
<hw>ge*ra"ni*ol</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Geranium</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A terpene alcohol
(<chform>C10H18O</chform>) which constitutes the principal part of the
oil of palmarosa and the oil of rose. Chemically it is
<chname>3,7-Dimethyl-2,6-octadien-1-ol</chname>. It has a sweet rose
odor.</def> <au>MI11</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

